OL,6,FThe Bank of England has raised its
OL,7,Fbase rate by a further 0.5 percentage
OL,8,Fpoints to hit a new 15-year-high of 5
OL,9,Fper cent, plunging tens of thousands
OL,10,Fof homeowners into mortgage misery.
OL,12,FIt is the 13th consecutive rise since
OL,13,FDecember 2021 when interest rates
OL,14,Fwere just 0.1 per cent. The ongoing
OL,15,Fincreases have put interest rates at
OL,16,Ftheir highest point since December
OL,17,F2008 and have resulted in the most
OL,18,Frapid increase in a short space of
OL,19,Ftime since the late 1980s.
OL,3,CBank of England raises interest rates
OL,4,Cto 15-year high of 5%
